20#define RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(x) \
21 do { \
22 if (!(x)) { \
23 return absl::nullopt; \
24 } \
25 } while (0)
26
27namespace {
28const int kMaxPicInitQpDeltaValue = 25;
29const int kMinPicInitQpDeltaValue = -26;
30} // namespace
31
32namespace webrtc {
33
34// General note: this is based off the 02/2014 version of the H.264 standard.
35// You can find it on this page:
36// http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-H.264
37
38absl::optional<PpsParser::PpsState> PpsParser::ParsePps(const uint8_t* data,
39 size_t length) {
40 // First, parse out rbsp, which is basically the source buffer minus emulation
41 // bytes (the last byte of a 0x00 0x00 0x03 sequence). RBSP is defined in
42 // section 7.3.1 of the H.264 standard.
43 std::vector<uint8_t> unpacked_buffer = H264::ParseRbsp(data, length);
44 rtc::BitBuffer bit_buffer(unpacked_buffer.data(), unpacked_buffer.size());
45 return ParseInternal(&bit_buffer);
46}
47
48bool PpsParser::ParsePpsIds(const uint8_t* data,
49 size_t length,
50 uint32_t* pps_id,
51 uint32_t* sps_id) {
52 RTC_DCHECK(pps_id);
53 RTC_DCHECK(sps_id);
54 // First, parse out rbsp, which is basically the source buffer minus emulation
55 // bytes (the last byte of a 0x00 0x00 0x03 sequence). RBSP is defined in
56 // section 7.3.1 of the H.264 standard.
57 std::vector<uint8_t> unpacked_buffer = H264::ParseRbsp(data, length);
58 rtc::BitBuffer bit_buffer(unpacked_buffer.data(), unpacked_buffer.size());
59 return ParsePpsIdsInternal(&bit_buffer, pps_id, sps_id);
60}
61
62absl::optional<uint32_t> PpsParser::ParsePpsIdFromSlice(const uint8_t* data,
63 size_t length) {
64 std::vector<uint8_t> unpacked_buffer = H264::ParseRbsp(data, length);
65 rtc::BitBuffer slice_reader(unpacked_buffer.data(), unpacked_buffer.size());
66
67 uint32_t golomb_tmp;
68 // first_mb_in_slice: ue(v)
69 if (!slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp))
70 return absl::nullopt;
71 // slice_type: ue(v)
72 if (!slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_tmp))
73 return absl::nullopt;
74 // pic_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
75 uint32_t slice_pps_id;
76 if (!slice_reader.ReadExponentialGolomb(slice_pps_id))
77 return absl::nullopt;
78 return slice_pps_id;
79}
80
81absl::optional<PpsParser::PpsState> PpsParser::ParseInternal(
82 rtc::BitBuffer* bit_buffer) {
83 PpsState pps;
84
85 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(ParsePpsIdsInternal(bit_buffer, &pps.id, &pps.sps_id));
86
87 uint32_t bits_tmp;
88 uint32_t golomb_ignored;
89 // entropy_coding_mode_flag: u(1)
90 uint32_t entropy_coding_mode_flag;
91 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(1, entropy_coding_mode_flag));
92 pps.entropy_coding_mode_flag = entropy_coding_mode_flag != 0;
93 // bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag: u(1)
94 uint32_t bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag;
95 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
96 bit_buffer->ReadBits(1, bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag));
97 pps.bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag =
98 bottom_field_pic_order_in_frame_present_flag != 0;
99
100 // num_slice_groups_minus1: ue(v)
101 uint32_t num_slice_groups_minus1;
102 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
103 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(num_slice_groups_minus1));
104 if (num_slice_groups_minus1 > 0) {
105 uint32_t slice_group_map_type;
106 // slice_group_map_type: ue(v)
107 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
108 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(slice_group_map_type));
109 if (slice_group_map_type == 0) {
110 for (uint32_t i_group = 0; i_group <= num_slice_groups_minus1;
111 ++i_group) {
112 // run_length_minus1[iGroup]: ue(v)
113 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
114 }
115 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 1) {
116 // TODO(sprang): Implement support for dispersed slice group map type.
117 // See 8.2.2.2 Specification for dispersed slice group map type.
118 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 2) {
119 for (uint32_t i_group = 0; i_group <= num_slice_groups_minus1;
120 ++i_group) {
121 // top_left[iGroup]: ue(v)
122 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
123 // bottom_right[iGroup]: ue(v)
124 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
125 }
126 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 3 || slice_group_map_type == 4 ||
127 slice_group_map_type == 5) {
128 // slice_group_change_direction_flag: u(1)
129 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(1, bits_tmp));
130 // slice_group_change_rate_minus1: ue(v)
131 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
132 } else if (slice_group_map_type == 6) {
133 // pic_size_in_map_units_minus1: ue(v)
134 uint32_t pic_size_in_map_units_minus1;
135 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
136 bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(pic_size_in_map_units_minus1));
137 uint32_t slice_group_id_bits = 0;
138 uint32_t num_slice_groups = num_slice_groups_minus1 + 1;
139 // If num_slice_groups is not a power of two an additional bit is required
140 // to account for the ceil() of log2() below.
141 if ((num_slice_groups & (num_slice_groups - 1)) != 0)
142 ++slice_group_id_bits;
143 while (num_slice_groups > 0) {
144 num_slice_groups >>= 1;
145 ++slice_group_id_bits;
146 }
147 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= pic_size_in_map_units_minus1; i++) {
148 // slice_group_id[i]: u(v)
149 // Represented by ceil(log2(num_slice_groups_minus1 + 1)) bits.
150 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
151 bit_buffer->ReadBits(slice_group_id_bits, bits_tmp));
152 }
153 }
154 }
155 // num_ref_idx_l0_default_active_minus1: ue(v)
156 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
157 // num_ref_idx_l1_default_active_minus1: ue(v)
158 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
159 // weighted_pred_flag: u(1)
160 uint32_t weighted_pred_flag;
161 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(1, weighted_pred_flag));
162 pps.weighted_pred_flag = weighted_pred_flag != 0;
163 // weighted_bipred_idc: u(2)
164 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(2, pps.weighted_bipred_idc));
165
166 // pic_init_qp_minus26: se(v)
167 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
168 bit_buffer->ReadSignedExponentialGolomb(pps.pic_init_qp_minus26));
169 // Sanity-check parsed value
170 if (pps.pic_init_qp_minus26 > kMaxPicInitQpDeltaValue ||
171 pps.pic_init_qp_minus26 < kMinPicInitQpDeltaValue) {
172 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(false);
173 }
174 // pic_init_qs_minus26: se(v)
175 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
176 // chroma_qp_index_offset: se(v)
177 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(golomb_ignored));
178 // deblocking_filter_control_present_flag: u(1)
179 // constrained_intra_pred_flag: u(1)
180 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(bit_buffer->ReadBits(2, bits_tmp));
181 // redundant_pic_cnt_present_flag: u(1)
182 RETURN_EMPTY_ON_FAIL(
183 bit_buffer->ReadBits(1, pps.redundant_pic_cnt_present_flag));
184
185 return pps;
186}
187
188bool PpsParser::ParsePpsIdsInternal(rtc::BitBuffer* bit_buffer,
189 uint32_t* pps_id,
190 uint32_t* sps_id) {
191 if (pps_id == nullptr)
192 return false;
193 // pic_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
194 if (!bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(*pps_id))
195 return false;
196 if (sps_id == nullptr)
197 return false;
198 // seq_parameter_set_id: ue(v)
199 if (!bit_buffer->ReadExponentialGolomb(*sps_id))
200 return false;
201 return true;
202}
